[The disease is due to a microsporidian and has commonly been observed in
oysters in France, certain Southeast Asia countries and in the New England
area of the US. It affects the Atlantic Oyster (_Crassostrea americanus_),
but doesn't appear to affect the Pacific oyster (_Crassostrea gigas_). In
some years, it has devastated the New England oyster fisheries. I'm not
aware of its causing devastation in the Gulf of Mexico, but not sure why
unless there is a temperature relationship. I would like to express my
grateful appreciation to Dr. Don Lewis for providing information regarding
this disease. - Mod.TG]
